audit_report:
YES, the contract is vulnerable due to the same denial of service issue. The vulnerability lies in the `ifillArray()` function with the loop:

```solidity
for(uint i=0; i<350; i++) {
    listAddresses.push(msg.sender);
}
```

This loop can result in excessive gas consumption when adding many addresses to the `listAddresses` array, especially as the array grows. This could cause the transaction to run out of gas, preventing the function from executing and causing a denial of service.
